Andorian ale was a blue-colored alcoholic beverage concocted by the Andorians. It was typically drunk from shot glasses. Enterprise NX-01 Captain Jonathan Archer developed a fondness for Andorian ale. (ENT: "Cease Fire")

In 2153, Commander Shran gave Archer several bottles of the drink. (ENT: "Proving Ground")

The Laikan Military Academy was an educational institute located on Andoria. This academy trained cadets for service in the Andorian military and provided extension courses through its Department of Foreign Studies to Starfleet officers.

In the first half of the 23rd century, Philippa Georgiou, when she was at Starfleet Command on Sol III, earned a diploma for Advanced Interstellar Combat from the Laikan Military Academy. In 2256, this diploma was displayed with her medals in the USS Shenzhou ready room. It bore the signatures of both the president of the academy and a vice admiral. (DIS: "The Vulcan Hello")

Bajoran marketplace was a holoprogram simulating a marketplace and mountain on Bajor.

In 2380, Ensigns Sam Rutherford and D'Vana Tendi called up the Bajoran marketplace simulation in an effort to escape from a malfunctioning and murderous Badgey. (LD: "Terminal Provocations")

The Gratitude Festival, also known as the Peldor Festival, was an annual holiday of great importance to the Bajoran people, which dated as far back as 17600 BC.

The traditional greeting during the festival was "Peldor joi". (DS9: "Fascination")

In 2371, Deep Space 9 hosted its third annual celebration of the Gratitude Festival. Kira Nerys served as presider of the Festival. Among the crowds were jugglers and dancers. (DS9: "Fascination")
